analysis: The documents primarily concern the withdrawal and reservation of public lands in California, often specifying the purpose of the withdrawal, such as for military use, coast guard, or forest protection. Many of the documents cite the Act of June 25, 1910, as amended, as the legal basis for these actions. Some orders revoke previous withdrawals or modify existing reservations. The documents frequently mention specific townships, ranges, and sections based on the San Bernardino Meridian or Mount Diablo Meridian.
title: California Land Management - Reservations and Withdrawals
